&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hop count is 2                                                         <br />
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Originating router is 8.8.8.8                                          <br />
                                                                               <br />
</code>
</div>
<p>
The interface GigabitEthernet1/0 has a default delay of 10 microseconds. The delay is increased from 10 microseconds to 
10000 microseconds. Note that the delay value entered is in tens of microseconds. This increases the metric of the path 
though interface GigabitEthernet1/0 and EIGRP then selects the path through interface FastEthernet3/0 as its metric is 
now considered the best.
</p>
<div style="background-color:#f4f0ec; border-style:solid;border-width:1px;border-color:#D3D3D3">
